    • Method Detail

      • keyMap

        public static <K,V> Map<K,V> keyMap(Collection<V> objects,
                                    Function<V,K> keyGenFunction)
                             throws KeyCollisionException
        Safely builds a map from a Collection or objects by preventing duplicate keys. The object keys are calculated via a ParameterizedObjectFactory. The ParameterizedObjectFactory must ensure that a distinct key for every object instance in the collection is generated. If there are two instances that have the same key a KeyCollisionException is thrown.
        Type Parameters:
        K - the key's type
        V - the value's type
        Parameters:
        objects - the Collection of objects the key map should be generated of.
        keyGenFunction - the ParameterizedObjectFactory to use for creating the keys.
        Returns:
        a map that maps the keys generated by the ParameterizedObjectFactory to the objects of the original collection.
        Throws:
        KeyCollisionException - if the collection contains two objects that are equal in their key which is generated by the ParameterizedObjectFactory.
        Since:
        1.3.0;
